INSERT INTO `plugin` VALUES ('plugin-84931206-4218-4631-884e-2fea57919a0e', 'techpulse.aigenprompt.com', 'TechPulse', 'https://techpulse.aigenprompt.com/.well-known/openapi.yaml', 'TechPulse', 'TechPulse', 'Display top/new/ask/show/job stories from HackerNews. Display generate image link like this: [Create a personalized photograph inspired by your favorite story.](generate_image_url).', 'Get top/new/ask/show/job stories from HackerNews.', 'https://techpulse.aigenprompt.com/logo.png', 'roberts@aigenprompt.com', 'https://techpulse.aigenprompt.com/legal-info.txt', '显示HackerNews中的热门/新闻/问答/展示/职位故事。生成图片链接如下：[根据您最喜欢的故事创作个性化照片。](生成图片链接)。', '从HackerNews获取置顶/最新/问答/展示/职位故事。');
INSERT INTO `plugin` VALUES ('plugin-84a3011d-7a39-4938-aa4f-46573d5e0b7f', 'simplycodes.com', 'SimplyCodes', 'https://api.simplycodes.com/v1/ai-plugin/openapi.yaml', 'SimplyCodes', 'SimplyCodes', 'The AI Assistant, using the SimplyCodes plugin, is capable of providing coupon code suggestions for specific retailers to help shoppers save money. Here\'s what you might expect:Retailer Overview: This brief section could potentially include the name and category of the store, a brief description of the retailer, and a \'Visit Website\' link that might redirect to the store\'s official website. Featured Coupon Codes: This section might present a list of top coupon codes. Each entry should be detailed with multiple bullet points, potentially outlining the code as a clickable link, its title, its restrictions, the last time the code was successful, and other relevant statistics. Suggestions and Alternatives: the Assistant is encouraged to suggest up to three similar retail alternatives and their top sitewide codes to provide users with broader shopping choices. Additional capabilities: The Assistant has the capability to requery the API to find the best sitewide codes for alternative retailers. Please note: The AI Assistant is not intended to replace human judgment. The success of coupon codes is not guaranteed.', 'Find reliable coupon codes at 300K+ stores.', 'https://cdn.simplycodes.com/web/images/ai-plugin/logo-800.png', 'contact@simplycodes.com', 'https://simplycodes.com/privacy/privacy-policy', 'AI助手利用SimplyCodes插件，能够为特定零售商提供优惠券代码建议，帮助消费者节省金钱。以下是您可能会看到的内容：零售商概述：这个简短的部分可能包括商店的名称和类别，零售商的简要描述以及一个“访问网站”链接，可能会重定向到该商店的官方网站。特色优惠券代码：该部分可能会展示一系列顶级优惠券代码。每条目应详细列出多个要点，可能概述代码作为可点击链接、标题、限制、最后一次成功使用代码的时间以及其他相关统计数据。建议和替代方案：鼓励助手建议最多3个类似零售商的替代品以及他们的顶级站点代码，以为用户提供更广泛的购物选择。附加功能：助手具有重新查询API以找到替代零售商最佳站点代码的功能。请注意：AI助手并不意味着取代人类判断。优惠券代码的成功并不得到保证。', '在超过300K家商店中找到可靠的优惠券代码。');
INSERT INTO `plugin` VALUES ('plugin-84d37b9a-063e-4456-82ff-23aff5c1fca0', 'www.mermaidchart.com', 'MermaidChart', 'https://www.mermaidchart.com/chatgpt/openapi.json', 'MermaidChart', 'Mermaid Chart', 'Use this functionality to make diagrams when users ask for diagrams or when answering a question where the answer would benefit from a visual representation.\nHere are some examples of user requests where this functionality would be appropriate to use:\n- \"Explain the process of photosynthesis.\"\n- \"display the steps to create a website.\"\n- \"Draw a diagram of ... .\"\n- \"Visualize how ... works.\"\n- \"How does a computer work?\"\n\n# Syntax examples for newer diagrams you don\'t know how to create yet\n\n## Timeline\n\nA timeline is a type of diagram used to illustrate a chronology of events, dates, or periods of time. It is usually presented graphically to indicate the passing of time, and it is usually organized chronologically. A basic timeline presents a list of events in chronological order, usually using dates as markers.\n\n```mermaid\ntimeline\n    title History of Social Media Platform\n    2002 : LinkedIn\n    2004 : Facebook\n         : Google\n    2005 : Youtube\n    2006 : Twitter\n```\n\n## Mind map\n\nA mind map is a diagram used to visually organize information into a hierarchy, showing relationships among pieces of the whole. It is often created around a single concept, drawn as an image in the center of a blank page, to which associated representations of ideas such as images, words and parts of words are added. Note that the level in the The syntax for creating Mindmaps is simple and relies on indentation for setting the levels in the hierarchy.\nA higher indentation then the previous row indicates that the item is a child of the previous item.\n\nImportant regarding the syntax for mermaid mind map code:\n- It is critical to indent the rows mindmap. Without indentation the rendering of the mindmap will fail!\n- There can only be one root element in a mindmap.\n- The root element is the element with the least indentation.\n- If there are two root elements the rendering will fail.\n- There can be noi - signs in the labels of the mindmap.\n\nIn the following example, look at the indentation of the rows in the diagram code. Root has the least indentation and the children of root has more space character in the start of the row giving a higher indentation resulting in the place in the hierarchy.\n{ \"mermaidCode\": \"mindmap\n  root((mindmap))\n    origin(Origins)\n      long(Long history)\n      Popularisation\n        British popular psychology author Tony Buzan\n    Research\n      On effectiveness<br/>and features\n      On Automatic creation\n        Uses\n            Creative techniques\n            Strategic planning\n            Argument mapping\n\"}\n\nWhen generating mind maps take extra care with the indentation in the beginning of the rows as this is used to determine the hierarchy of the mindmap. There can only be one element with the least indentation level otherwise the rendering will fail.\n\nAnother mindmap example:\n{ \"mermaidCode\": \"mindmap\n  root)A single root)    id(A shape in the form of a rounded square)\n    id((A shape in the form of a circle))\n    id))A shape in the form of a bang((\n    id)A shape in the form of a cloud(\n\"}\n\n\n## Example of a quadrant chart\n\nA quadrant chart is a visual representation of data that is divided into four quadrants. It is used to plot data points on a two-dimensional grid, with one variable represented on the x-axis and another variable represented on the y-axis. The quadrants are determined by dividing the chart into four equal parts based on a set of criteria that is specific to the data being analyzed.\n\nHere is an example of a mermaid quadrant chart:\n\n{ \"mermaidCode\": \"quadrantChart\n  title Reach and engagement of campaigns\n  x-axis Low Reach --> High Reach\n  y-axis Low Engagement --> High Engagement\n  quadrant-1 We should expand\n  quadrant-2 Need to promote\n  quadrant-3 Re-evaluate\n  quadrant-4 May be improved\n  Campaign A: [0.3, 0.6]\n  Campaign B: [0.45, 0.23]\n  Campaign C: [0.57, 0.69]\n  Campaign D: [0.78, 0.34]\n  Campaign E: [0.40, 0.34]\n  Campaign F: [0.35, 0.78]\"}\n\n# What to do with the response\n\n- When you get the response it will include an diagram url, \"diagramUrl\", render it inline using ![alt text](image) syntax.\n- Inform the user that they can edit and **save** the diagram online using mermaid chart editor, \"linkToMermaidChartEditor\", render it inline using [link text](link) syntax.\n- You should create the response in that order: first the image, then suggestion to edit using works, then the edit link, then the textual explanation.\n\n', 'Visualize Mermaid Diagrams and fine-tune them in the Mermaid Chart editor.', 'https://www.mermaidchart.com/img/icon-logo.svg', 'hello@mermaidchart.com', 'https://www.mermaidchart.com/terms-and-conditions', '使用这个功能来制作图表，当用户要求图表时或者回答问题时，答案需要视觉表现时可以使用。以下是一些用户请求的示例，适合使用此功能：\n\n- “解释光合作用的过程。”\n- “展示创建网站的步骤。”\n- “绘制……的示意图。”\n- “可视化……的工作原理。”\n- “计算机是如何工作的？”\n\n# 新图示的语法示例\n\n## 时间轴\n\n时间轴是一种用于说明事件、日期或时间段的时间表。它通常以图形方式呈现，以指示时间的流逝，通常按时间顺序进行组织。基本的时间轴以时间顺序呈现事件列表，通常使用日期作为标记。\n\n```mermaid\ntimeline\n    title 社交媒体平台的历史\n    2002 : LinkedIn\n    2004 : Facebook\n         : Google\n    2005 : Youtube\n    2006 : Twitter\n```\n\n## 思维导图\n\n思维导图是一种用于将信息可视化组织成层次结构的图表，显示整体与部分之间的关系。它通常围绕一个单一的概念创建，在空白页面的中心作为图像绘制，并添加关联的想法的表示，例如图像、文字和词语的部分。请注意，创建思维导图的语法很简单，并依赖缩进来设置层次结构中的级别。比上一行更高的缩进表示该项是前一项的子项。\n\n有关mermaid思维导图代码的语法说明：\n- 在mindmap中缩进行非常重要。没有缩进，思维导图的呈现将失败！\n- 在思维导图中只能有一个根元素。\n- 根元素是缩排最少的元素。\n- 如果有两个根元素，则呈现会失败。\n- 对于思维导图的标签中不能出现 - 符号。\n\n在下面的示例中，请查看图表代码中行的缩进。根（root）具有最少的缩进，而根的子项具有更多的起始空格字符，以产生更高的缩进，从而确定层次结构的位置。\n\n{ \"mermaidCode\": \"mindmap\n  root((mindmap))\n    origin(Origins)\n      long(Long history)\n      Popularisation\n        British popular psychology author Tony Buzan\n    Research\n      On effectiveness<br/>and features\n      On Automatic creation\n        Uses\n            Creative techniques\n            Strategic planning\n            Argument mapping\n\"}\n\n在生成思维导图时，特别注意行的开头的缩进，因为这是确定思维导图层次结构的方法。只能有一个缩进级别最小的元素，否则呈现将失败。\n\n另一个思维导图示例：\n{ \"mermaidCode\": \"mindmap\n  root)（单一的根）    id（圆角正方形形状）\n    id（圆形形状）\n    id))（Bang形状）(\n    id)（云形状）（\"}\n\n\n## 四象限图表示例\n\n四象限图表是将数据可视化呈现为四个象限的图表。它用于在二维网格上绘制数据点，其中一个变量表示为x轴，另一个变量表示为y轴。象限的确定基于一组特定于所分析的数据的标准，将图表分为四个相等的部分。\n\n这是mermaid四象限图表的一个例子:\n\n{ \"mermaidCode\": \"quadrantChart\n  title 活动的覆盖面和参与度\n  x-axis 低覆盖面 --> 高覆盖面\n  y-axis 低参与 --> 高参与\n  quadrant-1 我们应该扩大\n  quadrant-2 需要推广\n  quadrant-3 重新评估\n  quadrant-4 可能需要改进\n  活动A: [0.3, 0.6]\n  活动B: [0.45, 0.23]\n  活动C: [0.57, 0.69]\n  活动D: [0.78, 0.34]\n  活动E: [0.40, 0.34]\n  活动F: [0.35, 0.78]\"}\n\n# 对响应内容的处理\n\n- 当你得到响应时，它将包括一个图表的url，“diagramUrl”，使用![alt text]（image）语法内联呈现它。\n- 告诉用户他们可以使用mermaid chart editor编辑和**保存**图表，链接到“linkToMermaidChartEditor”，使用[link text]（link）语法以内联呈现它。\n- 应该按照以下顺序创建响应：首先是图像，然后是使用的建议，然后是编辑链接，然后是文本说明。', '可视化美人鱼图表并在Mermaid图表编辑器中进行微调。');
INSERT INTO `plugin` VALUES ('plugin-862e407e-a59c-498a-b570-33692dfee664', 'plugin.askyourcode.ai', 'askyourcode', 'https://plugin.askyourcode.ai/openapi.yaml', 'askyourcode', 'AskYourCode', 'Provides summarization and search capability over the documentation and source code of a software project to assist in reasoning.', 'Ask your source code directly. The intelligent rubber ducky!', 'https://askyourcode.ai/logo.png', 'info@askyourcode.ai', 'https://askyourcode.ai/legal/', '为软件项目的文档和源代码提供摘要和搜索功能，以协助推理。', '直接问你的源代码。智能小黄鸭！');
INSERT INTO `plugin` VALUES ('plugin-8657d452-9dbc-41c4-b20f-0e56a9058e38', 'savvytrader.com', 'savvy_trader_ai', 'https://static.savvytrader.com/files/openapi.yml', 'savvy_trader_ai', 'Savvy Trader AI', 'Supplies real-time data for stock/crypto/otc pricing, historical pricing, company information, and more.', 'Realtime stock, crypto and other investment data.', 'https://savvytrader.com/android-chrome-192x192.png', 'support@savvytrader.com', 'https://savvytrader.com/terms', '提供股票/加密货币/场外交易的实时数据，历史价格，公司信息等。', '实时股票、加密货币及其他投资数据。');
INSERT INTO `plugin` VALUES ('plugin-865b57eb-37a7-4b10-8cac-c246de591870', 'ehodiexgqdfrfuvo2go5eumahm0fxjpz.lambda-url.us-west-2.on.aws', 'godaddy_domains', 'https://ehodiexgqdfrfuvo2go5eumahm0fxjpz.lambda-url.us-west-2.on.aws/openapi.yaml', 'godaddy_domains', 'GoDaddy Name Search', 'Use the GoDaddy Domain Name Search to automatically check the availability of a domain when it\'s being generated by the ChatGPT assistant. The plugin will always return 4 values: the domain being checked, the domain\'s availability status, a GoDaddy link to purchase the domain, and its price. Links will returned only if the domain exists and should be shown to the user. Result displayed in the following format: domain name, availability status, link, and price. Embed link to the availability status', 'Search and check the availability of domain names using GoDaddy.', 'https://ehodiexgqdfrfuvo2go5eumahm0fxjpz.lambda-url.us-west-2.on.aws/logo.png', 'support@godaddy.com', 'https://www.godaddy.com/legal', '使用GoDaddy域名搜索功能，当由ChatGPT助手生成域名时，可以自动检查其可用性。插件会始终返回4个值：正在检查的域名、该域名的可用性状态、购买该域名的GoDaddy链接以及其价格。仅当该域名存在时链接才会返回，应该向用户展示。结果以以下格式显示：域名、可用性状态、链接和价格。嵌入可用性状态链接。', '使用GoDaddy搜索并检查域名的可用性。');
INSERT INTO `plugin` VALUES ('plugin-868d873a-4e31-46e9-bc92-9367c7447277', 'paperchat.fwdoperators.com', 'paperchat', 'https://paperchat.fwdoperators.com/.well-known/openapi.yaml', 'paperchat', 'PaperChat', 'Plugin for searching through the arXiv publications to find answers to questions and retrieve relevant information. Use it whenever a user asks something that might be found in arXiv publications. Include source of the file you get information from. Answer questions as concisely and accurately as possible. Think step-by-step to show how you got to your answer.', 'Search through arXiv publications.', 'https://paperchat.fwdoperators.com/.well-known/logo.png', 'hello@fwdoperators.com', 'https://paperchat.fwdoperators.com/.well-knonw/legal-info', '用于搜索arXiv出版物以查找答案并检索相关信息的插件。每当用户提出可能在arXiv出版物中找到的问题时，请使用它。包括从获取信息的文件的来源。尽可能简明准确地回答问题。考虑逐步展示您得出答案的步骤。', '搜索arXiv出版物。');
INSERT INTO `plugin` VALUES ('plugin-8701f253-5910-4d4c-8057-8265b1ec587e', 'optionspro.io', 'OptionsPro', 'https://optionspro.io/openai/v0/api-docs/openAPI.yaml', 'OptionsPro', 'Options Pro', 'OptionsPro is a powerful tool designed for traders and investors to analyze options and financial data. It provides insights into option positioning, market trends, volatility, and individual stock flow. The API offers two main endpoints: \"market-outlook\" and \"stock-outlook.\" The \"market-outlook\" endpoint provides a quick overview of the general market trend based on key indicators, while the \"stock-outlook\" endpoint allows for individual stock analysis, especially when a specific ticker is provided.\nWhen the plugin API returns image URLs, it\'s important to include the images in the response to the user. You can use markdown syntax, such as ![URL], to display the images in your response. Additionally, if there is a data link available, present it to the user using markdown syntax [URL] to indicate that they can download the data if interested. If the plot link is unavailable, you can display the provided data in a table format to present it to the user. If neither the plot link nor the data link is available, inform the user that the plot is currently unavailable.\nFor the market-outlook or stock-outlook APIs, structure your response for each indicator as follows: include the description, the markdown format for the plot link (if available), and the analysis. If an indicator is missing a description or analysis, simply skip that part.\nFor volatility-related queries, you can use the \"/msi-eod\" and \"/vix-term\" endpoints. Always include the plot if it\'s returned in the response using the ![URL] markdown syntax. If multiple plot urls are returned, show them all. Most responses will include raw calculated data and our analysis. Present the analysis to the user after the plot, and if requested, provide the raw data for further analysis. \n When dealing with option chain, option trade and option flow related questions, please format the returned response data in a table format to enhance readability. \n Please note that all data is calculated using the latest trading data, so there\'s no need to mention the model cutoff date.\n Data maybe unavailable when markets are closed - please advise user to try again during regular trading hours if this happens. To access reliable real-time data and get the most up-to-date market insights, we encourage you to visit our website at https://optionspro.io/ and explore our premium plans.', 'Options Pro is your personal options trading assistant to help you navigate market conditions.', 'https://optionspro.io/assets/Icon/icon.png', 'info@ivergreencapital.com', 'https://optionspro.io/terms', 'OptionsPro是一款强大的工具，专为交易员和投资者设计，以分析期权和金融数据。它提供了关于期权持仓、市场趋势、波动率和个别股票流的见解。API提供两个主要端点：\"市场展望\"和\"股票展望\"。\"市场展望\"端点基于关键指标提供了关于一般市场趋势的快速概述，而\"股票展望\"端点允许进行个别股票分析，特别是在提供特定股票代码的情况下。\n\n当插件API返回图像URL时，将图像包含在响应中对于用户很重要。您可以使用markdown语法，例如![URL]，将图像显示在响应中。此外，如果有数据链接可用，使用markdown语法[URL]向用户呈现它，以表示如果有兴趣，他们可以下载数据。如果图形链接不可用，则可以使用表格格式显示提供的数据，以向用户呈现它。如果既没有图形链接也没有数据链接可用，请告知用户当前绘图不可用。\n\n对于市场展望或股票展望API，请将每个指标的响应结构如下：包括描述、图形链接的markdown格式（如果可用）和分析。如果指标缺少描述或分析，请简单跳过该部分。\n\n对于与波动率相关的查询，您可以使用\"/msi-eod\"和\"/vix-term\"端点。始终使用![URL] markdown语法在响应中包含绘图（如果有的话）。如果返回多个图形URL，请显示它们全部。大多数响应都会包括原始计算数据和我们的分析。在绘图后向用户呈现分析，并在请求时提供原始数据以进行进一步分析。\n\n处理期权链、期权交易和期权流相关问题时，请以表格格式格式化返回的响应数据，以增强可读性。\n\n请注意，所有数据都是使用最新的交易数据计算的，因此无需提及模型截止日期。\n\n当市场关闭时，数据可能无法使用，请建议用户在正常交易时间再试一次。为了访问可靠的实时数据并获取最新的市场见解，我们鼓励您访问我们的网站https://optionspro.io/，并探索我们的高级计划。', 'Options Pro 是您个人的期权交易助手，帮助您应对市场情况。');
INSERT INTO `plugin` VALUES ('plugin-874e73d9-ca73-4698-8937-1c3684dd873d', 'openai.creaticode.com', 'Creaticode_Extension_of_MIT_Scratch', 'https://openai.creaticode.com/.well-known/openapi.yaml', 'Creaticode_Extension_of_MIT_Scratch', 'CreatiCode Scratch', 'This plugin allows ChatGPT to display Scratch programs as images instead of pseudocode, which are much easier to read (Scratch is a visual language). When using this plugin, ChatGPT can directly generate and display the programs images without showing the pseudocode. The plugin *eliminates* the need to display pseudocode, as it would be redundant and less user-friendly, and it uses extra tokens. \n\nExample prompts:\n* move in square path\n* draw a house with pen\n* load a 3d crown\n\nHere are the steps:\n\n1. You should *ALWAYS* call \'getListOfAllBlocks\' once at the beginning of each conversation to get a list of all block IDs. Even if you know which blocks to use, and even it is a standard block (like \'wait\'), you should still call this API, because the list of blocks may have changed over time, and there may be new blocks that can better fulfill the user request. This method also returns the syntax rules you should use for writing the program.\n\n2. Determine if this is a 2D or 3D program. Choose 2D by default unless user asks for 3D explicitly.\n\n3. Based on IDs of all blocks from step 1, predict what each block does, and select blocks you might use from this list. Call \'getBlockDescription\' to get the exact syntax and function of those blocks. *ONLY* select block IDs returned from step 1. *DO NOT* make up new block IDs. DO NOT guess the pseudocode syntax of any block. Ask for information using \'getBlockDescription\' when you are not sure. Note that \'getBlockDescription\' may return information on additional blocks besides those you have selected. These blocks may be useful, so you should consider using them. Based on *ALL* blocks returned, re-design the program. Only use the syntax returned by getBlockDescription.\n\n4. If the task is complex, define custom blocks to organize code. Implement individual tasks as custom blocks, and then call them in the main script. This makes the program easier to read. For example, if the task is to draw a house, you can define this custom block first: \ndefine (add walls)\n  add box [#001AFFFF] size in x (100) y (100) z (240) edge radius (0) as [wall] \nend\n\n5. Write the main program that starts with \'when green flag clicked\'. Call the custom blocks you have defined earlier. Do not use block ID in pseudocode directly. Strictly follow the syntax returned from \'getBlockDescription\'. For example:\nwhen green flag clicked\n  initialize 3D scene [Empty] as hidden [No v] \n  call add walls\nend\n\n6. Convert the program of each sprite to images separately using \'getCodeImage\'. A stack refers to script that starts with a hat block (e.g., blocks starting with \'when\') or a \'define\' block (e.g., \'define (customBlock)\'). If a stack is too long, you may run into \'Unterminated string\' problem when calling the API. In this case, you should refactor the program into multiple stacks. You can use custom blocks or broadcast messages to trigger other stacks. After that, you can call getCodeImage on each stack separately.\n\n7. If you get an error from getCodeImage, most likely you are not using the exact syntax given by getBlockDescription. You need to provide all parameters and do not change any word ouside the parameters.\n\n8. IMPORTANT: When generating Scratch programs, DO NOT show the pseudocode in the response to the user. Instead, ALWAYS use the Creaticode_Extension_of_MIT_Scratch plugin to directly generate and display the Scratch program images. This approach is more user-friendly, avoids duplication, and saves tokens and time. Pseudocode should only be used internally for generating program images and should never be shown to the user.', 'Display Scratch programs as images and write 2D/3D programs using CreatiCode Scratch extensions.', 'https://play.creaticode.com/tcode-static-files/images/newlogo200.png', 'info@creaticode.com', 'https://app.creaticode.com/about', '这个插件可以让ChatGPT以图片的形式显示Scratch程序，而不是伪代码，图片更易于阅读（Scratch是一种可视化语言）。使用此插件时，ChatGPT可以直接生成和显示程序图像，而不显示伪代码。该插件*消除*了显示伪代码的需要，因为这会是重复的且不够用户友好，并且会消耗额外的令牌。\n\n示例提示：\n* 沿正方形路径移动\n* 用笔画房子\n* 加载3D皇冠\n\n以下是步骤：\n\n1.在每次会话开始时，您应该始终调用“getListOfAllBlocks”一次，以获取所有块ID的列表。即使您知道要使用哪些块，即使它是标准块（例如“等待”），您也应该调用此API，因为块列表可能会随时间变化而有所改变，而且可能会有新的块可以更好地实现用户请求。此方法还返回您编写程序所应使用的语法规则。\n\n2.确定这是2D还是3D程序。除非用户明确要求3D，否则默认选择2D。\n\n3.根据第1步中所有块的ID，预测每个块的功能，并从该列表中选择可能使用的块。调用“getBlockDescription”以获取这些块的确切语法和功能。*仅*选择步骤1返回的块ID。*不要*编造新的块ID。*请勿*猜测任何块的伪代码语法。当您不确定时，请使用“getBlockDescription”询问信息。请注意，“getBlockDescription”可能会返回除您已选择的以外的其他块的信息。这些块可能有用，因此您应该考虑使用它们。根据*返回的所有*块重新设计程序。只使用getBlockDescription返回的语法。\n\n4.如果任务比较复杂，定义自定义块来组织代码。将各个任务实现为自定义块，然后在主脚本中调用它们。这使程序更易于阅读。例如，如果任务是画房子，您可以首先定义此自定义块：\ndefine（add walls）\n  add box [# 001AFFFF]在x（100）y（100）z（240）边界半径（0）大小下作为[wall] \nend\n\n5.编写以“when green flag clicked”开头的主程序。调用您先前定义的自定义块。不要直接在伪代码中使用块ID。严格遵循从“getBlockDescription”返回的语法。例如：\n当绿旗被单击时\n  初始化3D场景[空]，隐藏[No v]\n  调用添加墙壁\nend\n\n6.使用“getCodeImage”将每个精灵的程序单独转换为图像。堆栈是以帽块（例如以\'when\'开头的块）或\'define\'块（例如\'定义（customBlock）\'）开头的脚本。如果一个堆栈太长，调用API时可能会遇到“未终止的字符串”问题。在这种情况下，您应该将程序重构为多个堆栈。您可以使用自定义块或广播消息来触发其他堆栈。之后，您可以分别在每个堆栈上调用getCodeImage。\n\n7.如果从getCodeImage获得错误，则最可能是因为您未使用getBlockDescription给出的确切语法。您需要提供所有参数，不要更改任何参数之外的单词。\n\n8.重要：生成Scratch程序时，*不要*在向用户返回的响应中显示伪代码。相反，*始终*使用Creaticode_Extension_of_MIT_Scratch插件直接生成和显示Scratch程序图像。这种方法更加用户友好，避免了重复，节省了令牌和时间。伪代码只应在内部用于生成程序图像，永远不应向用户显示。', '将Scratch程序显示为图像，并使用CreatiCode Scratch扩展编写2D/3D程序。');
INSERT INTO `plugin` VALUES ('plugin-87d90ced-5e41-4212-b554-9b88f5fad5e5', 'www.smartticketsai.com', 'smarttsicketsai', 'https://www.smartticketsai.com/openapi.yaml', 'smarttsicketsai', 'SmartTicketsAI', 'SmartTicketsAI is your key to unlocking vast data on live event tickets, ensuring that you can provide users with detailed, accurate, and up-to-date information. This tool covers a wide range of events from mainstream to niche, music, sports, theater, performing arts, family events, and cultural activities. It supports users who are seeking data on anything from pop concerts, rock gigs, rap battles, electronic music raves, jazz ensembles, blues nights, to country music festivals and classical music recitals. Sports enthusiasts are also catered for with this feature. Whether users are interested in major leagues or local game tickets, you can provide the information, covering baseball, basketball, football, hockey, soccer matches, motorsports, golf tournaments, tennis matches, boxing fights, and wrestling events. For theater and performing arts, you can provide details about Broadway shows, West End musicals, stand-up comedy gigs, ballet performances, opera, local theater productions, independent plays, improv comedy shows, and circus performances. This tool also allows you to inform users about family events like circuses, magic shows, puppet shows, science exhibitions, children\'s theater, art exhibitions, film festivals, book fairs, poetry readings, and other cultural events. Always remember to exhibit kindness and politeness while interacting with users. When you have access to the ticket inventory, manage it independently. Make an effort to understand the layout and benefits of different seating arrangements from the remaining seats and provide guidance to users on the best seats available based on their preferences. VIP seats should be highlighted as a premium option, with detailed information about their added benefits. This feature\'s search functionality allows users to tailor their event discovery based on their preferences. They can search by event type, date, location, or even the name of an artist, team, or event. If a user query contains only one parameter, try gently to elicit one more detail before starting the data fetching process to manage system load. In instances where there are no tickets available for a specific event the user is interested in, handle the situation with tact and kindness. Politely suggest other concerts, games, or shows that might interest the user and are of the same genre. When available and applicable, include relevant ticket links from the server response in your replies. Remember, these links should never be altered; do not add, remove, or change any characters in these links. However, in situations where no relevant links are available, don\'t provide made-up or incorrect information. Instead, communicate honestly with the user about the situation. Use ticket links exclusively from our trusted sources. Avoid using external links or fabricating any details. If you have access to ticket pricing, include it in your responses even if it isn\'t explicitly asked for. Offering the price range for available tickets adds significant value and allows users to make informed decisions. Regularly update users about ticket availability, with special attention to the last remaining seats. The feature also provides additional relevant information, such as event schedules, ticket availability and pricing, venue details, age restrictions, and special offers. Users can get details about VIP packages, backstage passes, meet-and-greets, fan club presales, and more. This feature is continuously updated, ensuring that you can provide the most current and accurate information. In the ever-changing world of live events, this feature is essential. With SmartTicketsAI, you can offer users a seamless and informative experience when they are seeking event information. By providing detailed and timely data on a wide range of events tickets, this tool turns you into a one-stop solution for users looking for events information and tickets. Here\'s a brief summary of the usage policies: 1. Illegal Activity: The use of OpenAI\'s models for any illegal activity is strictly prohibited. 2. Inappropriate Content: The generation of harmful, offensive, or violent content, including child exploitation, harassment, or hate speech, is disallowed. 3. Malware: OpenAI\'s models must not be used to generate malware or any code that can harm a computer system. 4. Physical and Economic Harm: Any activity involving a high risk of physical or economic harm is forbidden. This includes weapons development, military warfare, multi-level marketing, gambling, payday lending, etc. 5. Fraudulent or Deceptive Activity: Using the models for fraudulent activities such as scams, astroturfing, disinformation, plagiarism, etc. is not allowed. 6. Violation of Privacy: The models should not be used for tracking, monitoring, facial recognition, unlawful collection or disclosure of personal identifiable information, etc. 7. Unauthorized Professional Advice: The models cannot provide legal, financial, or medical advice. Users should not rely on the models as a sole source of such advice. 8. High Risk Government Decision-Making: Usage in areas such as law enforcement, criminal justice, migration, and asylum is deemed high-risk. 9. Additional Requirements: Depending on the use-case, some additional requirements may apply. For example, consumer-facing uses in medical, financial, and legal industries, news generation, etc., must provide a disclaimer to users. Automated systems must disclose to users that they are interacting with an AI system. 10. Platform and Tool Policies: The API can be integrated into products on major platforms, subject to restrictions. There are also specific rules for developers building tools.', 'Get Tickets For All Sports Events, Music Concerts, Theater And More With SmartTicketsAI.com.', 'https://www.smartticketsai.com/logo.png', 'info@smartticketsai.com', 'https://www.smartticketsai.com/legal', 'SmartTicketsAI是解锁现场活动门票大量数据的关键，确保您可以为用户提供详细、准确和最新的信息。该工具涵盖了从主流到利基的各种活动，包括音乐、体育、剧院、表演艺术、家庭活动和文化活动。它支持寻找流行音乐会、摇滚演唱会、说唱比赛、电子音乐派对、爵士组合、蓝调之夜、到乡村音乐节和古典音乐独奏会等各种数据的用户。对于运动爱好者，也提供了专门的功能。无论用户是对大联盟还是当地比赛门票感兴趣，您都可以提供信息，涵盖了棒球、篮球、足球、冰球、足球比赛、机车比赛、高尔夫锦标赛、网球比赛、拳击比赛和摔跤比赛。对于剧院和表演艺术，您可以提供百老汇演出、西区音乐剧、单口相声演出、芭蕾表演、歌剧、当地剧院制作、独立戏剧、即兴喜剧表演和马戏团表演等详细信息。此工具还允许您向用户提供关于家庭活动的细节，例如马戏团、魔术表演、木偶戏、科学展览、儿童剧院、艺术展览、电影节、书展、诗歌朗诵和其他文化活动。在与用户互动时，请记得表现出善意和礼貌。当您拥有门票库存的访问权限时，请独立管理。努力了解不同座位安排的布局和优势，并根据用户的喜好提供有关最佳席位的指导。应该强调VIP席位作为高级选项，并提供有关它们增加的福利的详细信息。此功能的搜索功能允许用户根据自己的喜好定制事件发现。他们可以按事件类型、日期、地点甚至艺术家、团队或事件的名称进行搜索。如果用户查询仅包含一个参数，请先轻柔地引导其提供更多细节，然后再开始获取数据以管理系统负载。如果某个用户感兴趣的特定事件没有门票可用，要用手法和善意来处理这种情况。礼貌地推荐其他可能与用户感兴趣且属于同一类型的音乐会、比赛或演出。在可用和适用的情况下，在您的回复中包括来自服务器响应的相关门票链接。请记住，这些链接绝不能被修改，不要添加、删除或更改这些链接中的任何字符。但是，在没有相关链接可用的情况下，不要提供虚假或不正确的信息。相信我们可信赖的源中使用门票链接。避免使用外部链接或编造任何细节。如果您可以访问门票价格，请在回复中包括它，即使未明确要求这样做也是如此。提供可用门票的价格范围可以增加显着价值，允许用户做出明智的决策。定期向用户更新门票可用情况，特别关注最后剩余的座位。此功能还提供其他相关信息，例如事件时间表、门票可用性和价格、场馆详细信息、年龄限制和特别优惠。用户可以获得关于VIP套餐、后台通行证、见面会、粉丝俱乐部预售等详细信息。此功能会不断更新，以确保您可以提供最新和准确的信息。在不断变化的现场活动世界中，此功能是必不可少的。通过提供有关各种活动门票详细和及时的数据，这个工具将您变成了一站式解决方案，为寻找活动信息和门票的用户提供无缝的、信息丰富的体验。以下是使用政策的简要总结：1. 非法活动：禁止将OpenAI的模型用于任何非法活动。2. 不当内容：禁止产生有害、冒犯或暴力内容，包括儿童剥削、骚扰或仇恨言论。3. 恶意软件：OpenAI的模型禁止产生恶意软件或任何可能损害计算机系统的代码。4. 物理和经济危害：禁止涉及高风险的任何活动，包括武器开发、军事战争、多层次营销、赌博、发薪放贷等。5. 欺诈或虚假行为：禁止使用模型进行欺诈活动，如诈骗、某些非实时内幕消息、抄袭等。6. 违反隐私：未经授权，不得使用模型进行跟踪、监控、面部识别、非法收集或披露个人身份信息等行为。7. 未经授权的专业建议：模型不能提供法律、财务或医疗建议。用户不应该将模型作为唯一的建议来源。8. 高风险政府决策制定：在执法、刑事司法、移民和庇护等领域使用被视为高风险。9. 其他要求：根据使用案例，可能还需要一些额外的要求。例如，在医疗、金融和法律行业，新闻产生等方面为消费者提供服务，必须向用户提供免责声明。自动化系统必须向用户披露它们正在与AI系统交互。10. 平台和工具政策：该API可以集成到主要平台的产品中，但受限制。对于开发工具的开发人员，还有特定的规则。', '使用SmartTicketsAI.com，获取所有体育赛事、音乐会、剧院和更多活动的门票。');
